	<text id="ruskin_to_mother_july_22_1867">
	    
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>1996L00319</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>           
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q1025076" type="place">Keswick</rs>
	                </placeName>
	                <day>Monday,</day>
	                <date when="1867-07-22"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">22nd July 67.</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>To my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">mother</rs></salute><!-- match letter
	                exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	            
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">I was calling to-day on the <rs key="19199837" type="person">Mr [Butler]</rs>and <rs key="mrs_butler" type="person">Mrs. Butler</rs> of <rs key="Q34433" type="place">Oxford</rs>, who lost their little daughter by her falling downstairs (over the bannisters - she is a very sweet and nice person.</s>
	                <s id="s2">I imagine it was<hi rend="underline">he</hi> who must have taught the child to climb over the bannisters.</s>
	                <s id="s3">They are staying at the house on the island, <rs key="7451112" type="person">Mr. Marshalls</rs>, which is a very fine piece of <gap reason="illegible" unit="words" quantity="2"/> like gardening and building.</s>
	                <s id="s4"><rs key="7451112" type="person">Mr Marshall</rs> himself very like <rs key="35335176" type="person">John Lewis</rs> but seems nicer.</s>
	            </p>    
	
	            <p id="p2">    
	                <s id="s5">Afterwards, as it was raining and blowing hard, I could'nt row, so I climbing <rs key="Q4476111" type="place">Wallacrag</rs> and found <pb n="2"/> that I'm getting my limbs again gradually.</s>
	            </p>    
	
	            <p id="p3">    
	                <s id="s6">And that's all I can write to-day, for I was kept later by the rain, in reaching home.</s>
	            </p>
	            
	            <closer>
	                <salute>Ever my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs>, your most affectionate Son,</salute><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J. Ruskin.</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	
	            <pb n="3"/>
	
	            <postscript>
	                <p id="p4">    
	                    <s id="s7">I've written a line to Kate on her marriage - It's very hard having to congratulate everybody and never being married myself.</s>
	                </p>   
	            </postscript>
	
